# Movie Finder — Cursor / Antigravity Rules

This file is a legacy fallback. Cursor and Antigravity should load the MDC rules from `.cursor/rules/` instead — those files provide richer, file-type-aware context injection.

If your IDE supports MDC rules, the following files apply automatically:
- `.cursor/rules/project.mdc` — always active (project overview, submodule map, non-negotiables)
- `.cursor/rules/python.mdc` — active on `**/*.py` files (Python standards, backend patterns)
- `.cursor/rules/angular.mdc` — active on `**/*.ts`, `**/*.html`, `**/*.scss` (Angular standards)
- `.cursor/rules/architect.mdc` — active on architecture files + description-triggered
- `.cursor/rules/developer.mdc` — description-triggered when implementing issues
- `.cursor/rules/reviewer.mdc` — description-triggered when reviewing PRs
- `.cursor/rules/debugger.mdc` — description-triggered when investigating bugs
- `.cursor/rules/mentor.mdc` — description-triggered when explaining concepts
- `.cursor/rules/pm.mdc` — description-triggered for GitHub issue management

---

## Quick reference (fallback for IDEs that only read this file)

**Project:** Movie Finder — FastAPI + LangGraph 8-node AI pipeline + Angular 21 SPA + Qdrant Cloud + PostgreSQL 16.

**Non-negotiables:**
- Never `git add -A` — submodule state and secrets can be staged
- Never `--no-verify` on pre-commit
- Never push to `main` directly
- Never commit secrets
- Never instantiate shared resources inside route handlers — use FastAPI `Depends()`
- Never add `if provider == "openai":` branching — use the Strategy pattern
- Conventional Commits: `type(scope): summary`
- Disclose AI tool + model in every PR and review comment

**Python:** Python 3.13, `mypy --strict`, `ruff` (100 chars), no bare `except:`, no `os.getenv()`, async all the way.

**TypeScript:** Angular 21 standalone only, Signals for state, no `any`, strict mode, ESLint 9 + Prettier.

**Personas:** use `@architect`, `@developer`, `@reviewer`, `@debugger`, `@mentor`, `@pm` in chat, or see `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` for the full definitions.
